We also ordered the tzatziki and pita plate, it was a really good good sized portion of tzatziki and a lot of toasted pita. Of course the child only wanted chicken strips, the child is also a french fry connoisseur and he definitely gave his stamp of approval. We finished the meal with Greek coffee. reviews: [{"date":"3 weeks ago","id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURXNGJENGdBRRAB","name":"Jessie Pruitt","rating":"1 star","text":"Found an 8 yr old Camry hybrid on website. Went to look at it. I told them what I needed and John and the team made the magic happen. No pressure, just fair business. We appreciate you entrusting us with your purchase. Please let us know if you need anything else. Thanks again!"},{"date":"10 months ago","id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNxNEpuMkpBEAE","name":"Marshal Johnson","rating":"1 star","text":"For months now, we have had issues with our car we purchased from this place. We purchased the car with no AC with the guarantee that it would be fixed before we got the car. After receiving the car, the ac worked for about 3 to 4 months … We are very sorry to hear that we have failed to meet your expectations. The used car that your mother purchased was sold before the vehicle went through our used car inspection process and the A/C was not working and the car was still under warranty when it was purchased. When we put the vehicle through the inspection, we ran dye through the system and found where the compressor was leaking at the housing. No other leaks were found. We replaced the compressor and recharged the system under warranty. This was in April of 2020. In March of 2021, you brought the car back and said that the a/c didn’t work. By that time, the factory warranty had expired and the evaporator had a leak. Since the compressor was the only thing that was replaced in March of 2020, the warranty on it was extended for two years under the service parts warranty, so if the compressor had failed, it would have been covered under warranty again. The warranty on the rest of the A/C expired with the base warranty, and you elected to not purchase an extended warranty when you bought the car. Your mother called GM and started a CAC case with them because her mechanic said that there was a recall on the evaporator. There is a special coverage on some Impalas but the VIN number on your vehicle is not one that has the coverage due to the fact that your car has a different evaporator part number than the ones under the special coverage. Because your VIN was not covered, the CAC case was closed. Our service manager spoke with your mother numerous times and did run a policy calculator for her and subsequently, GM offered to pay all but 1000.00 of the repair which you opted not to take. We do feel we have done everything in our power to work with GM to come up with a solution."}]
